From: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 08:05:25 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm/damon/core: handle region split failure in
 apply_min_nr_regions()

This issue was discovered [1] by Sashiko.

[1] https://lore.kernel.org/20260717011834.120715-1-sj@kernel.org

Signed-off-by: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 mm/damon/core.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/mm/damon/core.c b/mm/damon/core.c
index 6ca84e7af2aa9..0095287ea81d8 100644
--- a/mm/damon/core.c
+++ b/mm/damon/core.c
@@ -2195,6 +2195,9 @@ static unsigned long damon_apply_min_nr_regions(struct damon_ctx *ctx)
 		damon_for_each_region_safe(r, next, t) {
 			while (damon_sz_region(r) > max_region_sz) {
 				damon_split_region_at(t, r, max_region_sz);
+				/* split might failed */
+				if (r == damon_last_region(t))
+					break;
 				r = damon_next_region(r);
 			}
 		}
-- 
2.47.3

